text = "Needles were used for various purposes over the course of time, including as sewing needles, but also as a part of traditional costume, whether as a hairpin or - as here - as a garment pin.

This pin was found in the area of the lower plateau of the Heuneburg and dates from the Hallstatt period (9th-5th century BCE). Clothing pins were used to fasten items of clothing, but also had a decorative character.

How and where these pins were attached to clothing can best be reconstructed on the basis of well-preserved grave finds.
"
